\section*{Reasons Behind the Current Situation}

The socio-political situation in India is driven by:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Hindu Nationalism}: The BJP’s promotion of Hindutva since the 1990s has intensified under Modi, leading to policies that critics argue marginalize minorities \citep{FreedomHouse2024}. This fuels communal tensions and hate speech.
    \item \textbf{Economic Disparities}: Despite growth, uneven distribution of wealth and high unemployment create social unrest \citep{Santandertrade2024}. Policies like “Make in India” aim to address this but face challenges \citep{OOSGA2023}.
    \item \textbf{Historical Legacies}: The caste system and colonial divisions continue to shape social and political structures \citep{Bartleby2011}.
    \item \textbf{Geopolitical Factors}: The Kashmir conflict, rooted in the 1947 partition, remains a flashpoint, with recent escalations adding to tensions \citep{AlJazeera2025}.
\end{itemize}

\section*{Impact on Indian Youth, Especially Gen Z}

India’s youth, particularly Gen Z, are significantly affected:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Political Engagement}: Gen Z is politically aware, with 50\% of 18–24-year-olds interested in politics, but low voter turnout reflects disillusionment with corruption \citep{IndianExpress2024}.
    \item \textbf{Economic Challenges}: Unemployment (12.4\% in 2023) and skill mismatches drive economic anxiety \citep{UserContext}. Many seek opportunities abroad \citep{WorldBank2023}.
    \item \textbf{Mental Health}: Communal polarization and social media exposure contribute to distress, with 51\% of youth affected \citep{Frontline2024}.
    \item \textbf{Migration Aspirations}: Global connectivity fuels aspirations to migrate, with many criticizing India’s socio-political climate \citep{GenZPolitics}.
\end{itemize}

\section*{Reasons for Migration to Western Countries}

Indian youth migrate to Western countries for:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Education}: Over 750,000 students studied abroad in 2022, attracted by prestigious universities and post-study work opportunities \citep{WorldBank2023}.
    \item \textbf{Economic Opportunities}: Higher wages in IT, healthcare, and engineering sectors draw migrants \citep{ImmigrantInvest2024}.
    \item \textbf{Quality of Life}: Better healthcare and infrastructure are significant pull factors \citep{EducationForAll2023}.
    \item \textbf{Socio-Political Stability}: Communal tensions push some to seek inclusive environments \citep{DrishtiMigration2024}.
\end{itemize}

\section*{Cultural and Racial Challenges for Indian Immigrants}

Indian immigrants face:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Cultural Differences}: India’s collectivist culture clashes with Western individualism, affecting workplace dynamics \citep{OasisIndia2024}.
    \item \textbf{Racial Discrimination}: Incidents like attacks on students in Australia (2009) and recent reports of bias persist \citep{BusinessToday2025}.
    \item \textbf{Integration Challenges}: Language barriers and lack of “local experience” hinder job prospects \citep{Frontiers2024}.
    \item \textbf{Contributions}: Despite challenges, Indians excel in technology and send \$120 billion in remittances annually \citep{IndianDiaspora2024}.
\end{itemize}

\section*{Why India Needs Its Diaspora Now}

The 35-million-strong diaspora is vital in 2025:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Economic Impact}: Remittances of \$120 billion in 2023 support development \citep{IndianDiaspora2024}.
    \item \textbf{Political Influence}: Diaspora leaders advocate for India’s interests \citep{VisionIAS2024}.
    \item \textbf{Cultural Soft Power}: Promoting Indian culture enhances global image \citep{DrishtiDiaspora2025}.
    \item \textbf{Innovation}: Expertise in technology and academia drives progress \citep{BBC2024}.
\end{itemize}

\section*{Role of Social Work}

Social work must:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Academic Integration}: Include migration and cultural competence in curricula \citep{ConferenceAlerts2025}.
    \item \textbf{Support Services}: Provide counseling and legal aid for migrants \citep{DrishtiMigrant2025}.
    \item \textbf{Policy Advocacy}: Push for inclusive migration policies \citep{CDPP2024}.
    \item \textbf{Diaspora Engagement}: Foster connections through cultural programs \citep{Indiaspora2024}.
\end{itemize}

\begin{table}[h]
\caption{Social Work Strategies for Migration and Diaspora Issues}
\begin{tabular}{p{3cm} p{6cm} p{3cm}}
